## iOS Mobile-First UI Guidelines

Design and implement UIs that feel native to iOS while remaining web-based.

### Goals
- **Mobile-first**: prioritize small screens and touch interactions; progressive enhancement for larger screens.
- **Feel native**: mirror iOS patterns (safe areas, navigation, gestures, motion, haptics cues).
- **Accessible**: 44×44pt touch targets, Dynamic Type-friendly, strong color contrast.

### Layout & Safe Areas
- **Viewport**: ensure `viewport-fit=cover` is set in the root document to use full screen and safe areas.
- **Safe area insets**: pad containers with `env(safe-area-inset-top/right/bottom/left)`.
- **Horizontal rhythm**: default page gutters 16px; card/list internal padding 16px; adhere to a 4px spacing grid.
- **Max width**: content is edge-to-edge on phone; for larger screens, center with a comfortable max width.
- **Scrolling**: one primary vertical scroll per screen; avoid nested scroll areas.

### Navigation Patterns
- **Navigation bar**: sticky top bar with title; supports large-title pattern that collapses on scroll.
- **Back navigation**: include a visible back affordance; support edge-swipe back when feasible.
- **Tab bar**: persistent bottom tab bar (≤5 tabs), translucent with safe-area padding; avoid hamburger menus.
- **Modals/Sheets**: present as bottom sheets or full-screen modals; include clear dismiss controls.
- **Search**: inline in nav bar or as a pull-down reveal beneath it; avoid separate search screens when possible.

### Components & Styling
- **Buttons**: primary filled (tint color), secondary tinted (outline or text), destructive in red; generous hit areas.
- **Lists**: grouped lists with separators; use chevrons for navigation rows; respect 56–60px row height.
- **Cards**: subtle corner radius (12–16px) and soft shadow; avoid heavy borders.
- **Segmented controls**: rounded segmented toggles for mode switching.
- **Toggles**: use switch for binary states; immediate feedback.
- **Sheets/Action panels**: rounded top corners, grabber indicator, safe-area bottom spacing.

### Typography
- **Font**: prefer San Francisco (system fonts) with fallbacks.
- **Scale**: base size 17px body; title1 28–34px (large title), headline 17px semibold, caption 13–15px.
- **Line height**: 1.25–1.5 depending on size; enable dynamic sizing where possible.

### Color & Theming
- **Semantic tokens**: define `tint`, `label`, `secondaryLabel`, `systemBackground`, `secondaryBackground`, `separator` for light/dark.
- **Translucency**: allow blurred translucent bars over content when supported.
- **Contrast**: meet WCAG AA; avoid low-contrast placeholder text.

### Motion & Interaction
- **Durations**: 180–280ms for UI transitions; 120–200ms for micro-interactions.
- **Easing**: springy, gentle curves; avoid linear; use `cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1)` for ease-out.
- **Gestures**: pull to refresh; swipe to go back (if safe); avoid hidden-only interactions.
- **Haptics**: map critical actions to light/medium impact (platform-permitting).

### Accessibility
- **Hit targets**: ≥44×44px; maintain spacing between interactive elements.
- **Dynamic type**: respect user font scale; avoid fixed-height text containers.
- **VoiceOver**: meaningful labels, traits/roles, ordered focus.

### Checklists
- Screen uses safe areas; nav/tab bars are translucent and padded for insets.
- Primary actions are reachable at bottom; destructive actions clearly marked.
- Single vertical scroll; large title collapses; content edges align to 16px grid.
- Touch targets ≥44px; color and motion considerate of accessibility settings.

